Acceptable use policy
Privacy policy
WonderPush is committed to protecting the privacy of your information. This Privacy Policy describes WonderPush’s Services privacy practices.
1. Scope
This Privacy Policy covers the information practices of:
https://www.wonderpush.com/
and
Software that we license and WonderPush related services (collectively “Platform”)
That can be used by our developer customers (each a “Developer(s)”) to send messages through their mobile Application(s) (each a “Application(s)”) to their users (each a “Final User(s)”).
2. Collected Information
As you navigate WonderPush.com, WonderPush may collect information through the use of commonly-used information-gathering tools, such as cookies and Web Site Navigational Information such as Web browser type and browser language, Internet Protocol (“IP”) address, and the actions you take on the WonderPush (such as the Web pages viewed and the links clicked).
When registering to use the Platform, WonderPush requires you to provide with personal contact information, such as name, company name, address, phone number, and email address (“Required Contact Information”). When purchasing the Platform’s services, WonderPush requires you to provide a billing name, billing address. Note that WonderPush doesn’t require you to provide a credit card number to purchase services as WonderPush uses third-party service provider (like PayPal) to manage credit card processing.
2.1 Information Collected in your Application(s) about your Final User(s):
When a Final User(s) is using one of your Application(s), your Application(s) collects various information that are sent via the SDK and stored in your WonderPush Cloud and used to perform the Platform:
(i) Login Data. WonderPush Services use the mobile device id and cookies to set up a Final User(s) account and/or to authenticate his use of the Application(s).
(ii) Mobile Device. WonderPush uses limited information from the Final User(s)’s mobile device in order to make available the Platform within the Application(s), such as device id, mobile device type, language.
(iii) Application(s)-Specific Information. WonderPush stores “Application(s)-specific Information”, which means information about each Final User(s) and the Application(s) they are using. This includes the Final User(s)’s user id, Application(s) sessions and duration.
3. Use of Collected Information
WonderPush uses data to perform the Platform’s service requested. For example, if you fill out a “Contact Me” Web form, WonderPush will use the information provided to contact you about your interest.
WonderPush uses Web Site Navigational Information to operate and improve the Platform.
WonderPush uses cookies that are session-based and persistent-based in order to facilitate navigation and to run services. When you provide WonderPush or a Application(s) with personal information, a unique identifier is assigned you. This unique identifier is associated with a persistent cookie that WonderPush places on your device. WonderPush is especially careful about the security and confidentiality of the information stored in persistent cookies. For example, WonderPush does not store account numbers or passwords in cookies.
Developer can access all his Final User(s)’s Collected Information such as device information and Application(s) usage.
WonderPush doesn’t use third party cookies to track and analyse usage into the Application(s).
WonderPush doesn’t share your Collected Information with third parties.
4. Correcting, Updating and Deleting
All of the collected data may give rise to the exercise of the right of access, rectification and opposition for legitimate reasons pursuant to the conditions and within the limits prescribed by Articles 38, 39 and 40 of Law no. 78-17 of January 6, 1978 as amended. In this regard, Final User(s) and Developer may obtain a copy of the personal data concerning themselves by sending a postal letter to WonderPush at the following address: 19, avenue d’Italie, 75013 Paris (France).
Developers may update, change their account information or delete all their personal data by logging in to their accounts at https://wonderpush.com. Requests to access, change, or delete their account and all their Collected Information will be handled within 30 days.
5. Security
WonderPush uses appropriate administrative, technical, and physical security measures to protect Data About WonderPush Customers.
6. Contacting Us
Questions regarding this Privacy Policy should be directed to privacy@wonderpush.com.